title: Area Girls Golf: Mid-County second at LTC meet
text: Posted Sep. 30, 2015 at 10:05 PM Posted Sep. 30, 2015 at 10:05 PM KEWANEE â€” Mid-County scored a 470 and finished second at the Lincoln Trail Conference Meet on Wednesday. Mercer County claimed the top three individual scores and finished with a 409 to win the meet. United took third with 514 and Annawan/Wethersfield was fourth with 560. Laura Meuller led the Cougars with a 107 and finished fourth overall. Elizabeth Whitford had a seventh-place score of 114, Emma Danner shot 118 and Alexis Haga had 131. The Red Storm were led by Erin Glisan with a 118 for ninth-place overall. Alex King shot a 125, Jaci Marshall scored 130 and Loren Fox tallied a 141. West Central was represented by three golfers led by Grace Scott with a 108. Scott finished the meet in fifth-place. Mia Lange shot a 130 and Carlee Link had 142 for the Heat. Jess Hankinson carded a 120 and Emily Hanson shot 130 for Williamsfield. The Register-Mail
